value: ***This file reproduces the results for the generalizability analysis reported in the manuscript and the web appendix.
***We draw on data collected in an MTURK online survey. In this case, we combine two waves of surveys, from July and October 2016
***Stata/IC 14.2 for Mac (64-bit Intel) was used for data analysis.
*drop conflict cases (i.e. rapproche=0) (This survey included an addional conflict treatment apart from neutral and rapprochement)
// drop if they did not get more than half of the manipulation checks right
*in some cases subjects coded more than one age variable: usually "18" and another. We treat the second age as the correct one.
* rescale to with min 0 max 1rename hawk5 hawk5_f
// now higher values now mean more internationalist
* count of meetings, sign, work for campaign, donate money to campaign
* recode best for ease of interpretation
